               <p>RICHARD MORRIS. I am a <rs id="t18270215-92-viclabel495" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-92-victim604 t18270215-92-viclabel495"></join>, and live in Skinner-street, Somer's-town. I lost a great coat on the 5th of February, at a quarter past three o'clock in the afternoon, off the back of my horse, in <placeName id="t18270215-92-crimeloc496">Old Fish-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270215-92-crimeloc496" type="placeName" value="Old Fish-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270215-92-crimeloc496" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-92-off493 t18270215-92-crimeloc496"></join>, while I was in a warehouse - when I had been in there ten or twelve minutes, I heard that a thief had ran away with it - I went out immediately, and pursued him with the warehouseman and another person; they ran faster than I - and the prisoner was brought back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270215-92-person605">
                  EDWARD 
                  CROSIER
               <interp inst="t18270215-92-person605" type="surname" value="CROSIER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270215-92-person605" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270215-92-person605" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was coming down Friday-street at a quarter past three o'clock that day - I met the prisoner and another young man; the prisoner was running, with this coat - I followed - he fell down - I took hold of him - he threw down the coat, and got away; I took it up, followed, and saw him taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270215-92-person606">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18270215-92-person606" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
